{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn1.58:1.1": "“Deviation” is <i lang='pi' translate='no'>uppatha</i> (“off course”). | These questions and answers are included in <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn1.76/en/sujato'>SN 1.76</a>. ",
    "sn1.58:1.4": "A reference to the belief that bathing in water brings purity. Compare the “inner bathing” at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/mn7/en/sujato#18.5'>MN 7:18.5</a>. ",
    "sn1.58:2.5": "“Fervor and celibacy” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>tapas</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>brahmacariya</i>) are closely linked in Atharva Veda 11.5, which eulogizes the brahmacārin as the force of potency creating even the gods. "
  },
